        "subject": "LU-2893 lod: OST0 is unused when offset is specified",
        "message": "LU-2893 lod: OST0 is unused when offset is specified\n\nIf a user specifies a non-zero OST index on which to start striping a\nfile, OST index 0 will never be used.  This is because the\nlod_alloc_specific() function neglects to record used OST indexes as\nit allocates OSTs. The array where the used indexes should have been\nstored is initialized with zero's, so it always appears that index 0\nis in use. Fix this by adding the missing statement to record used OST\nindexes.\n\nSigned-off-by: Ned Bass <bass6@llnl.gov>\nChange-Id: I4b5526950ce8c3f9739838855d86c6fdb56bfe61\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
